!!! 1.1
%html
    %head
        %title= @item[:title]

        - # Tiny link for Twitter & co.
        - if @item[:tiny]
            %link(rev="canonical" type="text/html" href="http://mutelight.org#{@item[:tiny]}")
        = render('_static_head')

    %body
        - content = yield
        #radial
            #wrapper
                #header
                    %h1.hide
                        %a(href="http://mutelight.org" title="Mutelight") Mutelight
                - if @item[:kind] == 'article'
                    = render('_article', :item => @item, :content => content)
                    = render('_other_articles', :reference_item => @item)
                - else
                    = content
                #about
                    %h2.hide About
                    :textile
                        p(important). I'm *Brandur Leach*, an engineer and developer operating out of Calgary, Canada doing work primarily in C#/.NET. This is Mutelight &mdash; my weblog. You should follow me on "Twitter (Brandur on Twitter)":http://twitter.com/fyrerise.

                        My current learning focus is functional languages like Clojure, Erlang, Haskell, and F#. At the moment I'm learning Haskell by hacking away on a "personal web framework":http://github.com/fyrerise/obsidian that uses CouchDB as its datastore.

                        I like learning guitar, "photography (Brandur on Flickr)":http://flickr.com/photos/brandurleach, "coding (Brandur on GitHub)":http://github.com/fyrerise, "listening to power and symphonic metal (Brandur on last.fm)":http://www.last.fm/user/fyrerise, and tennis. I prefer working on systems with a terminal, but I spend most of my time under Windows at work. Everything that I write is done in Vim.

                        div(#articles). "Archive (Article archive)":/archive.html

                        E-mail me anytime at *(mail)brandur@mutelight.org*.
                %br
                %br
